<subSubSection pageNumber="529" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="529">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="529">Note:</emphasis>
Wijnands (
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="529">Bot. Commelins</emphasis>
: 84. 1981) argued that the typification by Roessler should be rejected because the thesis in which 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Othonna" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageNumber="529" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rigens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="529">Othonna rigens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was published was based largely on specimens lent to Linnaeus by Burman. While this is generally true, 1027.3 (LINN, above) is annotated as 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Othonna" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageNumber="529" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rigens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="529">Othonna rigens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by Linnaeus, and appears to be original material for both that name and 
<taxonomicName authority="(L.) L. (1763)" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1763" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1760" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Gorteria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageNumber="529" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rigens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="529">Gorteria rigens</emphasis>
(L.) L. (1763)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Roessler’s" pageNumber="529">Roessler's</normalizedToken>
typification is accepted here.
</paragraph>
